## Integral citations

### Without positions

````
Hello [+@foo] and [+@bar]
.
<p>Hello <a class="citation" href="#cite1" role="doc-citation">Foo (1943)</a> and <a class="citation" href="#cite2" role="doc-citation">Bar (1989)</a>
````

### With positions

````
Hello [+@foo, p. 42]
.
<p>Hello <a class="citation" href="#cite1" role="doc-citation">Foo (1943, p. 42)</a>
````

### With multiple references

````
Hello [+@foo, p. 42; @bar; @baz, fig. 5]
.
<p>Hello <a class="citation" href="#cite1" role="doc-citation">Foo (1943, p. 42), Bar (1989), Baz (2123, fig. 5)</a>
````

## Non-integral citations

### Without positions

````
Hello [@foo] and [@bar]
.
<p>Hello <a class="citation" href="#cite1" role="doc-citation">(Foo 1943)</a> and <a class="citation" href="#cite2" role="doc-citation">(Bar 1989)</a>
````

### With positions

````
Hello [@foo, p. 42]
.
<p>Hello <a class="citation" href="#cite1" role="doc-citation">(Foo 1943, p. 42)</a>
````

### With multiple references

````
Hello [+@foo, p. 42; @bar; @baz, fig. 5]
.
<p>Hello <a class="citation" href="#cite1" role="doc-citation">(Foo 1943, p. 42), (Bar 1989), (Baz 2123, fig. 5)</a>
````

